<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🐉 M003 Week 6 — English Worksheet (Intermediate)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Recreate the Ender Dragon (x, y, z) · <strong>Course:</strong> 3D Coordinates · <strong>Level:</strong> Intermediate · <strong>Time:</strong> about 40 minutes</p>
<p>A big blocky <strong>ender dragon</strong> stands in your world — black blocks, purple eyes. A big model is just a set of <strong>parts</strong>: a long <strong>body</strong>, a <strong>head</strong> at the front, and two <strong>wings</strong> that spread out. Today you build the body, the head, and two simple wings. Every block uses <strong>(x, y, z)</strong> — x <strong>across</strong>, y <strong>up</strong>, z <strong>forward</strong> (deep). The body is <strong>long along z</strong>. The wings <strong>spread along x</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🔴 Stand on your <strong>home spot</strong> (red block) every run. Move your feet, move your head.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each code. Write your full prediction.</p>
<pre><code>fill black from (0, 6, 0) to (0, 6, 8)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>One block wide, long along z. Across, up, or deeper? How long?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>fill black from (1, 6, 4) to (4, 6, 4)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>This is one wing. Which number changes? Does it go left/right (x), up (y), or deep (z)?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>fill black from (0, 6, 0) to (0, 6, 8)
place black block at (0, 7, 9)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>The body, then the head. Is the head in front of the body or behind it? Higher or same height?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — This should be a <strong>long body</strong> running deep (along z), from (0, 6, 0) to (0, 6, 8). Right now it is only one block.</p>
<pre><code>fill black from (0, 6, 0) to (0, 6, 0)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B</strong> — This should be a <strong>wing</strong> spreading out to the side (along x), from (1, 6, 4) to (4, 6, 4). Right now it grows <strong>up</strong> instead of out.</p>
<pre><code>fill black from (1, 6, 4) to (1, 9, 4)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Look at the dragon in your world. Walk around it. Then build your own on your home spot, part by part:</p>
<pre><code>fill black from (0, 6, 0) to (0, 6, 8)
place black block at (0, 7, 9)
fill black from (1, 6, 4) to (4, 6, 4)
fill black from (-4, 6, 4) to (-1, 6, 4)
</code></pre>
<p>That is body, head, right wing, left wing. Add two <strong>purple</strong> eye blocks on the head. Make the wings match — same length on both sides.</p>
<p>Send a photo or video. Then finish these — 4 to 6 sentences.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>First, I built the body. It runs deep, so I changed the … number.</p>
<p>My head block is at (x = …, y = …, z = …).</p>
<p>The right wing goes from ( … , … , … ) to ( … , … , … ).</p>
<p>To make the left wing match, I …</p>
<p>One tricky moment was when …</p>
<p>If I had more time, I would …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Film yourself showing your dragon. Use these words: <strong>x</strong>, <strong>y</strong>, <strong>z</strong>, <strong>body</strong>, <strong>head</strong>, <strong>wing</strong>, <strong>home spot</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show your home spot. Why stand on it every run?</li>
<li>Point at the body. Say which number made it long.</li>
<li>Point at one wing. Say which number made it spread out.</li>
<li>Show that both wings are the same length.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Plan what you will say:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
